        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         <em>
          (I bought an iPad so I could make beautiful drawings like this)
         </em>
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         Remote Co can attract A players from anywhere in the world, including Local Co\xe2\x80\x99s hometown. Local Co is left with the B and C players in its hometown.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         Last year, Stripe made
         <a href="https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFUMtuhSAQ_RrZ1QCCxQWLbvobBnBUchEMDG38-3J10WSSyTzPwxmELeVLn6kgqQXy7BfNRq4GKSayaLEwJRXxZV4zwGF80JgrkLPa4J1Bn-J9QSmXZNcrKGkFVcqIwfJpcsoJIZkF0RYGuZI3zmzq4iE60PAD-UoRSNA74lm64avj3y0KZn9C79LRChvS1lKGIyF87NUSrznllLGBssZTDD3rR5nlFcZpFNAJemy8L9UWNO71_kKyjgltyj5ubfzazQHhHjQhc8tHjR6vGaKxAZZHIz6u3JTxOkFH-C0BECE_zSacU8U-JzaRhrak5k_8B_oDqkh2QA" style="color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">
          Remote
         </a>
         its fifth engineering hub, in addition to San Francisco, Seattle, Dublin, and Singapore. This September, it
         <a href="https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkE2OhCAQhU_T7DCA4uiCRW_mGgahWkkjGCjaePtBezEJSRWvfl7lMxphielUe8xISoY0Oat4L4ZWdiOxqrN8kANxeXolgE07rzAVIHuZvTMaXQz3BGNCklX1ohtGPrARetsbzrTg0Frgc2ukhddALp9JF-sgGFDwgXTGAMSrFXHPj_b5EL_1HcfR-Lp9g9yYuFVlLtkFyLmmCGYN0cflrJ-M9fwaBROMspFyeYvJ7UAP5z3d9UmPmN6QMr1aGKMY6RY_QHGFQE3BK3Hp6iROXYs4bxmvBLq24U0vkzx9P_YdPDq2LaLJZc6ozfs6jSQVIs4xubDU8nvVG_i7UBFNNW4lODwnCHr2YL_08Mv7hoHnDirAkT0gQvqKFalgA_8Z-Uiqm42VfPg3-gOZLZUd" style="color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">
          offered employees $20,000
         </a>
         upfront (with a potential cost of living pay reduction) to move out of the Bay Area, New York, or Seattle. Already a desirable place to work, Stripe can attract the best talent from anywhere in the world with the promise that they will be equally important to the employees in the four physical hub cities.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         On the other end of the spectrum, imagine a company that plans to make employees come back to the office five days a week. Assuming that most employees have gotten comfortable working from home and like the flexibility of at least a Hybrid option, and will look for jobs at companies that offer Hybrid or Remote work, this company is left with the people who:
        </p>
        <ol style="margin: 1em 0;">
         <li style="margin: 3.75px 0 3.75px 7.5px; mso-special-format: bullet;">
          <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0;">
           Live in or near the city in which their office is located.
          </p>
         </li>
         <li style="margin: 3.75px 0 3.75px 7.5px; mso-special-format: bullet;">
          <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0;">
           Don\xe2\x80\x99t want to work for a Remote or Hybrid company or couldn\xe2\x80\x99t get a job at the Remote or Hybrid company of their choice.
          </p>
         </li>
        </ol>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         It\xe2\x80\x99s not just tech employees, either. I have one lawyer friend who just chose one offer over another because its location was going to be more flexible, and another friend in finance who told me that he\xe2\x80\x99s going to look for a new job as soon as his firm asks him to come back to the office.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         If you choose to Return, you\xe2\x80\x99re essentially making a bet that the benefits of all being in the same office every day outweighs the risks of attracting lesser talent and potentially losing your best employees. Mayyyyybe you make that trade if you assume that physical and digital solutions will remain exactly as they are today. But they won\xe2\x80\x99t. They\xe2\x80\x99re already improving.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         <em>
          Continue reading online to learn about what companies can do to adapt their physical and digital tools to Remote and Hybrid work, and a thought experiment on the implications of a world in which we never go into the office every day ever again.
         </em>
        </p>
